article.headline: New Mexico 55, Colorado State 47
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Danny Granger had 11 points and 10 rebounds to lead New Mexico over Colorado State 55-47 on Saturday night. Ryan Wall added 12 points, and Alfred Neale had 10 for New Mexico (17-5, 4-3 Mountain West) in a sloppy game for both teams. New Mexico shot 31 percent from the field, but Colorado State (9-11, 1-6) shot just 30 percent. The Lobos also scored 13 points off turnovers. New Mexico used an 11-3 run to pull ahead 48-38 with less than six minutes to go, but Colorado State was within three twice in the last 2½ minutes. Seven free throws by New Mexico sealed the victory for the Lobos. Matt Nelson scored 16 for CSU, and Sean Morris had 15 points and a career-high nine rebounds, but no other Rams scored in double digits.
